        <abstract> 
<p>Comments on Richard Owen’s review of the <hi rend="italic">Origin</hi> [in <hi rend="italic">Edinburgh Rev.</hi> 111 (1860): 487–532]. Considers Owen unfair to CD and most ungenerous toward Hooker.</p>  
<p>Expects Sedgwick to be fierce against him. Sedgwick also misrepresented CD in his <hi rend="italic">Spectator</hi> review [24 Mar and 7 Apr 1860].</p> 
            <p>Compares natural selection to the undulatory theory of light as a hypothesis explaining a large number of facts.</p>
        </abstract>
